@node Understand what ‘armouring' means in Dezyne and what it is used for
@subsection Understand what ‘armouring' means in Dezyne and what it is used for

You can use armouring to protect a Dezyne generated system against
misbehaving foreign code.  This was discussed in
@ref{Definition and usage of armouring}

@node Identify how to apply 'armouring' in Dezyne
@subsection Identify how to apply 'armouring' in Dezyne

To understand how to apply armouring you must study the contents of
@ref{Definition and usage of armouring} and at least one example in
@ref{Armouring patterns}.

@node Understand the different 'armouring' patterns
@subsection Understand the different 'armouring' patterns

The section @ref{Armouring patterns} provides an example for all
possible invidual armour cases.

